      "description": "One-loop massless triangle integral with three off-shell external legs ($x_1=p_1^2, x_2=p_2^2, x_3=(p_1+p_2)^2$) in $d=4$, with general conformal weights specialized to $c_0=4, c_1=c_2=c_3=2$ (unit propagator powers $\\nu_1=\\nu_2=\\nu_3=1$). The integral satisfies a system of three conformal second-order PDEs generating a holonomic $D_3$-ideal $I_3$ of rank 4. The four linearly independent solutions (eq. 2.11) span the analytic continuation space and are expressed in terms of dilogarithms $\\operatorname{Li}_2$ and logarithms. Canonical series solutions are computed via the SST (Saito-Sturmfels-Takayama) algorithm and independently recovered via Wasow's method for Fuchsian systems. Singular locus: $\\{x_1=0\\} \\cup \\{x_2=0\\} \\cup \\{x_3=0\\} \\cup \\{\\lambda=0\\}$ where $\\lambda = x_1^2+x_2^2+x_3^2-2(x_1 x_2+x_1 x_3+x_2 x_3)$.",
